deep in the heart of texas is a 1942 black-and-white western released in the united states starring johnny mack brown as a man instrumental in restoring texas . it was directed by western director elmer clifton . the film is situated during the american civil war in texas . the film is best known for its performance of american folk song " deep in the heart of texas " which is sung by country singer tex ritter with jimmy &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; trio .